Introduction

About Jeffrey Lin

Hi everyone! My name is Jeffrey Lin and I am a current candidate for a Master of Science in Biostatistics at Columbia University Mailman School of Public Health. I completed my undergraduate education at Tufts University, graduating with a BS in Cognitive and Brain Sciences, as well as a minor in Computer Science. My research interests generally focus on designing models which can aid in the classification and prediction of diseases for patients. In my free time, I enjoy playing basketball and practicing Judo and Brazilian Jiu Jitsu.
